# AZUS Resource Files List
# ============================================================
# This file controls which companion files are:
#   1. Copied from Resources/ into each dataset staging folder
#   2. Listed in file_list.csv (with SHA-512 hash and size)
#   3. Added to the ZIP archive under the ESID_XXX/ subfolder
#   4. Uploaded separately to Zenodo
#
# HOW TO ADD A NEW COMPANION FILE:
#   1. Place the file in your Resources/ folder
#   2. Add one row below with its name, type, description, and
#      associated data dictionary (use N/A if none)
#   3. Run prepare_dataset.py as normal — no code changes needed
#
# COLUMNS:
#   File Name                 — exact filename (must match file in Resources/)
#   File Type                 — human-readable format label
#   Description               — one sentence describing the file's purpose
#   Associated Data Dictionary — filename of companion data dict, or N/A
#
# DO NOT INCLUDE in this list:
#   - README.md               (auto-generated from README_template.html)
#   - total_eclipse_data.csv  (auto-generated from collector CSV)
#   - file_list.csv           (auto-generated — the file list itself)
#   - CONFIG.TXT              (comes from AudioMoth device, not Resources/)
#   - *.WAV files             (come from AudioMoth device, not Resources/)
#   - related_identifiers.csv (managed separately — see CITATIONS_USER_GUIDE.md)
#   - references.csv          (managed separately — see CITATIONS_USER_GUIDE.md)
#
# ============================================================
File Name,File Type,Description,Associated Data Dictionary
your_data_dict.csv,Comma Separated Variable (.CSV),Data dictionary for your primary data file.,N/A
License.txt,Plain Text (.txt),Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0) license text.,N/A
YourDevice_Operation_Manual.pdf,Portable Document Format (.PDF),Device operation manual.,N/A
